# Windows batch files MUST keep CRLF line endings, or cmd.exe misparses
# multi-line `if (...)` blocks and goto labels and the window closes instantly.
# eol=crlf forces CRLF in the working tree on every platform (incl. WSL),
# so a future `git add --renormalize` can never silently convert them to LF.
*.bat   text eol=crlf
*.cmd   text eol=crlf

# Keep shell scripts LF regardless of platform.
*.sh    text eol=lf
